    },
    "This parameter can be used to control the personality of the model. The more imaginative, the more unstable the output. This parameter is also known as temperature." : {
      "localizations" : {
        "de" : {
          "stringUnit" : {
            "state" : "translated",
            "value" : "Dieser Parameter steuert die Persönlichkeit des Modells. Je fantasievoller, desto instabiler die Ausgabe. Auch bekannt als Temperatur."
          }
        },
        "en" : {
          "stringUnit" : {
            "state" : "translated",
            "value" : "This parameter can be used to control the personality of the model. The more imaginative, the more unstable the output. This parameter is also known as temperature."
          }
        },
        "es" : {
          "stringUnit" : {
            "state" : "translated",
            "value" : "Este parámetro controla la personalidad del modelo. Cuanto más imaginativo, más inestable la salida. También se conoce como temperatura."
          }
        },
        "fr" : {
          "stringUnit" : {
            "state" : "translated",
            "value" : "Ce paramètre contrôle la personnalité du modèle. Plus il est imaginatif, plus la sortie est instable. Aussi appelé température."
          }
        },
        "ja" : {
          "stringUnit" : {
            "state" : "translated",
            "value" : "このパラメータでモデルのパーソナリティを制御できます。想像力を上げるほど出力は不安定になります（いわゆる temperature）。"
          }
        },
        "ko" : {
          "stringUnit" : {
            "state" : "translated",
            "value" : "이 매개변수는 모델의 성격을 조정합니다. 상상력을 높일수록 출력이 불안정해집니다. temperature로도 알려져 있습니다."
          }
        },
        "zh-Hans" : {
          "stringUnit" : {
            "state" : "translated",
            "value" : "此参数可用于控制模型的性格。想象力越丰富，输出越不稳定。此参数亦可称为温度。"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "This PDF has %lld page(s). You can select whether to import it as text or convert it to images." : {
      "localizations" : {
        "de" : {
          "stringUnit" : {
            "state" : "translated",
